OL,3,C'No watering down of Hillsborough Law'
OL,4,Cahead of first debate
OL,6,FHe said: "We will do everything we can
OL,7,Fto pass this legislation in its
OL,8,Fcurrent, strong form. We welcome
OL,9,Fscrutiny that sharpens the Bill ` but
OL,10,Fwe will not allow the principles that
OL,11,Fgive the Hillsborough Law its meaning
OL,12,Fand purpose to be watered down.
OL,14,F"With this monumental piece of
OL,15,Flegislation, we will help deliver our
OL,16,FPlan for Change by making sure that
OL,17,Ftruth and justice will no longer have
OL,18,Fto be prised from closed doors, and
OL,19,Fthat families seeking answers will
OL,20,Fnever again be left to fight alone."
OL,26,@nD@JOUvD@AOU|D@dO]
