OL,3,C'No watering down of Hillsborough Law'
OL,4,Cahead of first debate
OL,6,FThere will also be a new offence for
OL,7,Fmisleading the public, which the
OL,8,FGovernment said will mean criminal
OL,9,Fsanctions for the most serious
OL,10,Fbreaches.
OL,12,FPaula Sussex, the parliamentary and
OL,13,Fhealth service ombudsman, said the new
OL,14,Fduty of candour "can be a defining
OL,15,Fmoment in how our democracy works".
OL,17,FShe said: "The provisions in this Bill
OL,18,Fwill go a long way to rebuild that
OL,19,Ftrust between government and people.
OL,26,@vD@QOUwD@bO]yD@KOU
